{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_014xPak34DynRcrWgfMFWNQS","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"CockroachDB is running in `--insecure` mode, so:\n- Port 8080 serves HTTP (not HTTPS) for the DB Console\n- Port 26257 handles SQL traffic without TLS\n\nSo for the Ingress:\n- I do NOT need `backend-protocol: HTTPS` annotation\n- I just need a regular HTTP ingress with TLS termination at nginx (nginx handles TLS, proxies HTTP to the backend)\n\nFor the TLS secret, I need to create a self-signed certificate for `crdb-ui.example.com`.\n\nLet me proceed:\n\n1. Create self-signed TLS cert and secret in cockroachdb namespace\n2. Set up the Ingress for the DB Console, then configure the ingress-nginx controller to handle SQL traffic on port 26257 by creating a tcp-services ConfigMap and patching the controller deployment and service to expose that port. I should also verify whether the controller's container ports need updating.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":517,"cache_read_input_tokens":32703,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":517},"output_tokens":39,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a9fcb28a-3e89-4606-9a12-fb3bad91b6ce","uuid":"d6422b06-3096-40bc-a5d9-46aadb8994a9","request_id":"req_011CccxQKRAbpbzpfxkbSazu"}
